```rust
// Constants
const SIGMA: f64 = 165.7366171829776;
const SIGMIN: f64 = 1.2778336969128337;
const SIG_BOUND: i64 = 34034726;
const SIG_BYTELEN: usize = 666;
const HEAD_LEN: usize = 1;
const LOGN: u8 = 9;  // log2(512)
pub const PUBLIC_KEY_LEN: usize = 896;  // 512 * 14 bits / 8
pub const SIGNATURE_LEN: usize = 666;

// Error type
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum FalconError {
    InvalidPublicKey,
    InvalidSignature,
    InvalidSecretKey,
    SignatureNormTooLarge,
    DecompressionFailed,
}

// Core data structures
pub struct SecretKey {
    f: [i32; N],                    // NTRU secret polynomial f
    g: [i32; N],                    // NTRU secret polynomial g
    capital_f: [i32; N],            // NTRU secret polynomial F
    capital_g: [i32; N],            // NTRU secret polynomial G
    b0_fft: [[Vec<Complex>; 2]; 2], // Basis B0 in FFT representation
    tree: LdlTree,                  // LDL tree for fast sampling
}

pub struct VerifyingKey {
    h: [i32; N],  // Public key h = g/f mod (X^n + 1, q)
}

pub struct Signature {
    header: u8,           // Encodes log2(n)
    salt: [u8; SALT_LEN], // 40-byte random salt
    s1_enc: Vec<u8>,      // Compressed signature polynomial s1
}

pub struct Falcon<H: HashToPoint> {
    _marker: PhantomData<H>,
}
```

**SecretKey Methods:**

- `pub fn to_bytes(&self) -> Vec<u8>` - Serializes as `f || g || F || G` (4×896 bytes)
- `pub fn from_bytes(bytes: &[u8]) -> Result<Self, FalconError>` - Deserializes and reconstructs `b0_fft` and LDL tree

**VerifyingKey Methods:**

- `pub fn from_h(h: [i32; N]) -> Self`
- `pub fn h(&self) -> &[i32; N]`
- `pub fn to_bytes(&self) -> [u8; PUBLIC_KEY_LEN]` - 896 bytes
- `pub fn from_bytes(bytes: &[u8; PUBLIC_KEY_LEN]) -> Result<Self, FalconError>`

**Signature Methods:**

- `pub fn from_components(header: u8, salt: [u8; SALT_LEN], s1_enc: Vec<u8>) -> Self`
- `pub fn to_bytes(&self) -> Vec<u8>` - Header (1) + salt (40) + compressed s1 (625)
- `pub fn salt(&self) -> &[u8; SALT_LEN]` - Access embedded salt
- `pub fn from_bytes(bytes: &[u8]) -> Result<Self, FalconError>`

**Falcon<H> Methods:**

- `#[cfg(feature = "shake")] pub fn keygen() -> (SecretKey, VerifyingKey)` - Uses system RNG
- `pub fn keygen_with_seed(seed: &[u8]) -> (SecretKey, VerifyingKey)` - Deterministic from seed
- `pub fn keygen_with_rng<F: FnMut(usize) -> Vec<u8>>(random_bytes: &mut F) -> (SecretKey, VerifyingKey)` - Custom RNG
- `#[cfg(feature = "shake")] pub fn sign(sk: &SecretKey, message: &[u8]) -> Signature` - Random salt
- `pub fn sign_with_salt(sk: &SecretKey, message: &[u8], salt: &[u8; SALT_LEN]) -> Signature` - Deterministic
- `pub fn sign_prehashed(sk: &SecretKey, hash_point: &[i16; N], seed: &[u8; SEED_LEN]) -> (Vec<i32>, Vec<i32>)` - Returns (s0, s1) polynomials
- `pub fn verify(vk: &VerifyingKey, message: &[u8], sig: &Signature) -> Result<bool, FalconError>`

### 6. **Hash-to-Point Trait**

**File:** `/home/felt/PycharmProjects/falcon-rs/src/hash_to_point.rs` (118 lines)

```rust
pub trait HashToPoint {
    type Input;
    fn hash_to_point(message: &[Self::Input], salt: &[Self::Input]) -> [i16; N];
}

// SHAKE256 implementation
#[cfg(feature = "shake")]
pub struct Shake256Hash;

#[cfg(feature = "shake")]
impl HashToPoint for Shake256Hash {
    type Input = u8;
    fn hash_to_point(message: &[u8], salt: &[u8]) -> [i16; N]
}
```

Uses rejection sampling with `k = floor(2^16 / Q)` for uniform distribution over Zq.

### 7. **Poseidon Hash Implementation**

**File:** `/home/felt/PycharmProjects/falcon-rs/src/poseidon_hash.rs` (107 lines)

```rust
pub type Felt = FieldElement<Stark252PrimeField>;

pub struct PoseidonHashToPoint;

impl HashToPoint for PoseidonHashToPoint {
    type Input = Felt;

    fn hash_to_point(message: &[Felt], salt: &[Felt]) -> [i16; N] {
        // 1. Absorb: poseidon_hash_span(message || salt) -> single felt252 seed
        // 2. Squeeze: 21 full hades_permutations (504 coeffs) + 1 partial (8 coeffs) = 512
        // 3. Extract: 12 Zq per felt252 via DivRem-by-Q on (low u128, high u128)
    }
}
```

**Key Design:**
- Uses `lambdaworks` PoseidonCairoStark252 for Starknet compatibility
- Matches Cairo implementation exactly
- 22 permutations total: 21 full + 1 partial
- Extracts 6 coefficients from low u128, 6 from high u128 per felt252

### 8. **Encoding Module**

**File:** `/home/felt/PycharmProjects/falcon-rs/src/encoding.rs` (240 lines)

```rust
// Signature compression: sign + low 7 bits + unary high bits
pub fn compress(v: &[i32], slen: usize) -> Option<Vec<u8>>
pub fn decompress(x: &[u8], n: usize) -> Option<Vec<i32>>

